This paper deals with mining commonsense knowledge from raw text using knowledge base completion models. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the critical analysis of the difficulty of mining novel commonsense knowledge, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
